WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.540 --> 00:00:07.310
Okay so, today we are very fortunate to have
Ayelet Waldman here with us to speak. Ayelet

00:00:07.310 --> 00:00:13.080
is the author of New York Times best seller
"Bad Mother: A Chronicle of Maternal Crimes,

00:00:13.080 --> 00:00:19.380
Minor Calamities and Occasional Moments of
Grace"; "Love and Other Impossible Pursuits",

00:00:19.380 --> 00:00:25.779
"Daughter's Keeper" and the "Mommy-Track Mysteries".
Her personal essays have been published in

00:00:25.779 --> 00:00:32.250
a wide variety of newspapers, magazines including
the New York Times, The Guardian, The San

00:00:32.250 --> 00:00:40.430
Francisco Chronicle, Elle Magazine, Vogue,
Allure, Cookie, Child, Parenting, Real Simple,

00:00:40.430 --> 00:00:46.790
Health and Salon.com. Her radio commentaries
have appeared on "All Things Considered" and

00:00:46.790 --> 00:00:55.200
"The California Report". The film version
of "Love and Other Impossible Pursuits" with

00:00:55.200 --> 00:01:01.670
Don Ross as screen writer and director and
Natalie Portman in the lead role is set to

00:01:01.670 --> 00:01:09.220
premier at the Toronto Film Festival in September
2009. Her books are published throughout the

00:01:09.220 --> 00:01:16.660
world in countries such as England and Thailand,
the Netherlands and China, Russia and Israel.

00:01:16.660 --> 00:01:17.780
So, without further ado, Ayelet.

