Um, so I got my editor to do it, and she also
was, she's, apparently there's, my favorite

00:14:28.019 --> 00:14:32.019
part of all the horrible things they says
is that whenever anybody says anything nice

00:14:32.019 --> 00:14:37.139
about me or my books someone always says,
according to my editor, 'Hello Ayelet we know

00:14:37.139 --> 00:14:43.040
it's you'. [laughter]. Like I'm spending all
my days on Urban. I mean there was a time

00:14:43.040 --> 00:14:48.989
in my life where I probably would have spent
more time on Urban Baby, but not so much now.

00:14:48.989 --> 00:14:55.129
So during 2005 and 2006 I had a column on
Salon.com that kinda replaced the Andy Lamont

00:14:55.129 --> 00:15:00.019
Mommy column and in that column I wrote on
all sorts of subjects. I wrote on motherhood,

00:15:00.019 --> 00:15:05.529
yes, but I also wrote on, for example, my
own mother's battles with Medicare, the rights

00:15:05.529 --> 00:15:12.499
of juvenile defendants, how much weight I
gain every Christmas season. I tried to be

00:15:12.499 --> 00:15:16.059
timely, I tried to be honest and I tried to
write with humor about difficult subjects.

00:15:16.059 --> 00:15:21.879
By the time I published my second column I
had completely stopped looking at the comments

00:15:21.879 --> 00:15:29.050
section so many people wrote, and while many
responses were sort of vaguely complimentary,

00:15:29.050 --> 00:15:35.139
