shower, why? Um, that was not, obviously,
my first experience with being loathed on

00:17:23.870 --> 00:17:28.750
the internet, which is, as you can tell, the
subject of today's little talk. Um I had,

00:17:28.750 --> 00:17:33.920
as some of you might have known, might have
ready many, I guess it was about 5 years ago

00:17:33.920 --> 00:17:38.730
now. I published an essay in the New York
Times that really kind of brought me, not

00:17:38.730 --> 00:17:42.490
a lot of people read Salon, so they were haters
on Salon, but with the New York Times, it

00:17:42.490 --> 00:17:49.900
turns out that more than 5 million people
read. And I wrote this essay, I wrote it for

00:17:49.900 --> 00:17:56.880
a literary anthology, and we're going to do
a little experiment now. How many of you have

00:17:56.880 --> 00:18:01.020
ever read a literary anthology? Okay, so,
this is an educated crowd. That was like six

00:18:01.020 --> 00:18:08.610
hands. How many who broke, how many of you
read the whole thing? Yeah. Three. Okay? [laughter].

00:18:08.610 --> 00:18:13.560
There's my point. What happened was two friends
of mine were putting together this literary

00:18:13.560 --> 00:18:17.180
anthology that nobody was going to read and
they, it was all about motherhood and they

00:18:17.180 --> 00:18:22.060
called me and said, alright Ayelet, we've
got mothers writing about divorce, and we've

00:18:22.060 --> 00:18:24.990
got mothers writing about having twins and
we've got mothers writing about breast cancer,

00:18:24.990 --> 00:18:29.160
but we don't have any mother writing about
sex. And since you're the only person we know

00:18:29.160 --> 00:18:35.140
that's having any [laughter] you have to write
about it. And, um I decided that I would for

00:18:35.140 --> 00:18:39.270
this anthology that nobody would read and
at first I wrote this kind of Dr. Ruthie how

00:18:39.270 --> 00:18:43.710
to maintain an intimate relationship with
your husband when you have 4 children piece.

00:18:43.710 --> 00:18:50.420
But the more I got into it, the more I always
can, I can always find that sort of corrosive

00:18:50.420 --> 00:18:55.130
sense of ribbon of self-loathing in every
topic and I realized that this whole idea

00:18:55.130 --> 00:18:59.380
of my sex life made me feel horrible. It made
me feel like an awful mother, it made me feel

00:18:59.380 --> 00:19:05.440
bad about myself, and I wrote about that.
So, I'll just give, I'll read you like the

00:19:05.440 --> 00:19:09.970
